        {
            "title": "Bitcoin, Ethereum, Dogecoin prices slide due to inflation concerns. Ethereum dips to $3,680.37 after hitting $4,000 peak.",
            "id": "d269585f-729d-4e6e-bf86-2ddfde1e6897",
            "description": "Leading cryptocurrencies, including Bitcoin, Ethereum, and Dogecoin, experienced a decline along with stocks due to a rise in consumer prices leading to fears of no interest rate cuts. Prices at 9:40 p.m. ET showed Bitcoin down by 2.17% at $115,531.73, Ethereum down by 3.77% at $3,680.37, and Dogecoin down by 5.72% at $0.2084. Bitcoin hit an intraday low of $114,369.87, causing a market-wide decrease. Long traders suffered losses as over $570 million in long positions were wiped out in 24 hours. Despite this decline, Bitcoin and Ethereum had profitable July with Bitcoin gaining nearly 8% and Ethereum soaring over 48%. Bitcoin's open interest fell by 0.86%, and Ethereum saw a 1.83% drop in unsettled contract funds. The Crypto Fear & Greed Index indicated weakening \"greed\" sentiment in the market. In the past 24 hours, top gainers were Toncoin with +2.00% at $3.49, XDC Network with +1.77% at $0.09785, and Story (IP) with +1.16% at $6.02. The global cryptocurrency market capitalization was at a steady level.",
            "link": "https://www.markets.news/headlines/d269585f-729d-4e6e-bf86-2ddfde1e6897",
            "pub_date": "2025-08-01 10:26:13",
            "source": "unusualwhales",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        }
